Tecpro Expects 3.5-Billion Rupee Orders From NTPC, Grasim

-- B y   H e m a l   S a v a i
-- 
2011-03-30T09:34:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/tecpro-expects-5-5-billion-rupees-of-orders-from-ntpc-grasim.html
Tecpro Systems Ltd. (TPRO) , an Indian
engineering company, is the lowest bidder for a 3.5 billion
rupees ($78 million) order from the nation’s biggest power
producer, Chief Financial Officer Kulbhushan Arora said.  New Delhi-based Tecpro bid for a project to manage and
process coal and ash supplies for NTPC Ltd., Arora said. The
order may be awarded in the quarter ending June 30, he said.
The company may win an order from Grasim Industries Ltd., the
world’s largest maker of viscose staple fiber, worth more than 2
billion rupees, in the same period, Arora said.  The company’s shares advanced 2.1 percent to 275.5 rupees
at 2:56 p.m. in Mumbai, a seventh straight day of gains. The
stock has dropped 32 percent from its close of 405.7 rupees on
Oct. 12 when trading began.  Sales may climb 38 percent to 20 billion rupees in the year
ending March 31 and profit may rise by as much as 35 percent,
Arora said, without providing a number. Net income was 1.09
billion rupees in the year ended March 2010, according to data
compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
